WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:13.320
Well, where are we now?

00:13.320 --> 00:16.360
What do we have in Hume's universe?

00:16.360 --> 00:21.840
We have a bundle of impressions or experiences, images, and so on.

00:21.840 --> 00:23.880
Impressions of what?

00:23.880 --> 00:25.800
Nothing.

00:25.800 --> 00:29.980
External world is a myth.

00:30.620 --> 00:33.940
Experiences experienced by whom?

00:33.940 --> 00:35.100
Nobody.

00:35.100 --> 00:38.180
The self is a myth.

00:38.180 --> 00:42.940
Now you might think this is as far as we can go in skepticism.

00:42.940 --> 00:46.820
Impressions of nothing by nobody.

00:46.820 --> 00:50.420
But there is more to go yet.

00:50.420 --> 00:58.980
There is one very famous and incredibly influential point of Hume's that is almost universally accepted today by philosophers.

00:58.980 --> 01:10.460
There is still one more link tying the world or tying experiences together, which must be shattered if we're to end up with a real poached egg mentality.

01:10.460 --> 01:15.420
And that is the law of cause and effect.

01:15.420 --> 01:20.220
Remember Barclay had believed in cause and effect coming from God.

01:20.220 --> 01:22.260
Hobbes had believed in cause and effect.

01:22.260 --> 01:27.060
Every major philosopher prior to Hume believed in cause and effect.

01:27.100 --> 01:33.940
Hume now sets his nominalism and sensualism to work to demolish cause and effect too.

01:33.940 --> 01:37.860
So now we'll look at Hume's greatest quote achievement.

01:37.860 --> 01:43.020
His destruction of the law of cause and effect.

01:43.020 --> 01:45.140
Well again, we follow the standard procedure.

01:45.140 --> 01:48.220
Let's take the term cause.

01:48.220 --> 01:50.060
What does it mean?

01:50.060 --> 01:53.940
We say A causes B.

01:53.940 --> 01:55.660
Take a classic simple example.

01:55.660 --> 01:58.340
We take a rock and throw it at a window.

01:58.340 --> 01:59.460
The window shatters.

01:59.460 --> 02:03.980
We say the rock caused the window to break.

02:03.980 --> 02:08.420
What does it mean to say one thing caused another?

02:08.420 --> 02:13.700
Well says Hume, people think that there are three points involved.

02:13.700 --> 02:15.980
Two of them as we'll see are OK.

02:15.980 --> 02:21.020
One, the vital one proves to be meaningless.

02:21.020 --> 02:26.300
Well one thing involved in the causal relationship is spatial contiguity.

02:26.300 --> 02:29.140
Togetherness in space.

02:29.140 --> 02:35.300
The rock actually touches the window for instance in the process of it breaking.

02:35.300 --> 02:36.620
Well that's very simple.

02:36.620 --> 02:39.740
We can see the two of them in direct physical contact.

02:39.740 --> 02:45.740
So we have a direct perceptual reference for the phrase spatial contiguity or spatial togetherness.

02:45.740 --> 02:48.380
And therefore that's perfectly meaningful.

02:48.380 --> 02:50.420
But that of course is not enough.

02:50.460 --> 02:55.380
Causal relationship also involves temporal contiguity.

02:55.380 --> 03:00.740
The window breaks immediately after in time the rock strikes.

03:00.740 --> 03:05.740
And again says Hume, that's a perfectly respectable phrase temporal contiguity

03:05.740 --> 03:11.740
because we can observe one thing happening immediately after another in time

03:11.740 --> 03:15.100
and therefore that is perfectly meaningful.

03:15.140 --> 03:22.660
But spatial and temporal contiguity after all do not yet give us the essence of the causal relationship.

03:22.660 --> 03:26.700
A coincidence can have these two characteristics.

03:26.700 --> 03:30.900
For instance suppose I casually touch this lecture.

03:30.900 --> 03:38.820
And while I'm in direct contact with it spatially, at the next instant it suddenly gives off,

03:38.820 --> 03:43.940
I don't know, 13 bombs in the whole room and whole building come down.

03:43.940 --> 03:49.740
Well you would say maybe the two events were spatially and temporally connected

03:49.740 --> 03:51.500
but that simply is a coincidence.

03:51.500 --> 03:53.300
There's no causal connection.

03:53.300 --> 03:57.780
Maybe someone in the next room let off a bomb at the same instant.

03:57.780 --> 04:04.340
What is the crucial factor, the vital ingredient in the concept of causal connection?

04:04.340 --> 04:08.740
Well says Hume, it is necessary connection.

04:08.740 --> 04:13.580
Not only spatial and temporal contiguity but necessary connection.

04:13.620 --> 04:19.460
When we say A causes B, we mean more than simply the two go together in space

04:19.460 --> 04:21.620
and the two go together in time.

04:21.620 --> 04:25.900
We mean that the first necessitates the second.

04:25.900 --> 04:29.940
That the two have a compulsory connection to each other.

04:29.940 --> 04:33.980
That granted the first the second must happen.

04:33.980 --> 04:37.380
That the first produces the second.

04:37.380 --> 04:40.220
That the first makes the second happen.

04:40.220 --> 04:45.540
Etc. All those being synonyms for necessary connection.

04:45.540 --> 04:53.980
Well now let us put this strand, necessary connection to the test of the theory of meaning.

04:53.980 --> 05:04.020
Do we ever perceive or form an image of necessary connection between events?

05:04.020 --> 05:05.620
Now watch it very closely.

05:05.620 --> 05:12.060
I don't have a window here to demonstrate but you just have to project that I take a rock

05:12.060 --> 05:17.020
and I throw it at the window and you see the rock sailing slowly across the room.

05:17.020 --> 05:23.100
Then you see, now you can stand there you right next to the wall with a magnifying glass to watch.

05:23.100 --> 05:26.700
You see the rock moving, touch the window.

05:26.700 --> 05:30.180
So far there's no necessity, there's just a rock, right?

05:30.180 --> 05:33.420
The next thing you see the fragment shattered, right?

05:33.420 --> 05:41.060
Now no little flag came out and said, the next event is unavoidable.

05:41.060 --> 05:47.940
There was no booming voice from the sky that said, what comes now has to be.

05:47.940 --> 05:54.740
There was no Doris Day saying K-Sara-Sara.

05:54.740 --> 05:59.340
We perceive that two events go together in space and time, that's all.

05:59.340 --> 06:04.420
We never come in contact with any such phenomenon as necessity.

06:04.420 --> 06:06.060
What is necessity like?

06:06.060 --> 06:07.420
Is it red?

06:07.420 --> 06:08.740
Is it loud?

06:08.740 --> 06:10.460
Is it a heart?

06:10.460 --> 06:13.620
Well, can you form an image of it?

06:13.620 --> 06:14.940
What does it look like?

06:14.940 --> 06:16.980
What would it taste like?

06:16.980 --> 06:20.380
Obviously we cannot form a perceptive necessity.

06:20.380 --> 06:23.940
We cannot form an image of necessity.

06:24.020 --> 06:30.220
It must therefore be an utterly meaningless term.

06:30.220 --> 06:35.780
The phrase necessary connection must be just noise, like gloop.

06:35.780 --> 06:40.860
And so of course must any of its synonyms, the synonym of nonsense is nonsense.

06:40.860 --> 06:44.540
And therefore when you say one thing produces another or makes it happen or

06:44.540 --> 06:50.660
given the first, the second must happen, all of those are equally meaningless.

06:50.660 --> 06:57.780
Now let's have Hume speak for himself on this, quote.

06:57.780 --> 07:02.140
First, he states his nominalism and sensualism, quote.

07:02.140 --> 07:06.020
It seems a proposition which will not admit of much dispute,

07:06.020 --> 07:11.820
that all our ideas are nothing but copies of our impressions.

07:11.820 --> 07:13.300
That's his sensualism, you see.

07:13.300 --> 07:18.620
An idea is simply a faded copy of your sense experience.

07:18.620 --> 07:20.460
To be fully acquainted, I'm continuing the quote.

07:20.460 --> 07:25.500
To be fully acquainted, therefore, with the idea of necessary connection,

07:25.500 --> 07:27.740
let us examine its impression.

07:29.060 --> 07:31.980
In order to find the impression with greater certainty,

07:31.980 --> 07:36.380
let us search forward in all the sources from which it may possibly be derived.

07:37.660 --> 07:42.660
Now, unquote, now he conducts a scrupulous search all over the place,

07:42.660 --> 07:45.540
looking for a necessary connection if only he could find it.

07:45.540 --> 07:51.300
And, quote, when we look about us towards external objects and

07:51.300 --> 07:57.300
consider the operation of causes, we are never able in a single instance to

07:57.300 --> 08:00.100
discover any power or necessary connection.

08:01.220 --> 08:05.020
Any quality which binds the effect to the cause and

08:05.020 --> 08:08.740
renders the one an infallible consequence of the other.

08:08.740 --> 08:14.820
We only find that the one does actually, in fact, follow the other.

08:14.820 --> 08:18.740
There is not in any single particular instance of cause and

08:18.740 --> 08:24.780
effect anything which can suggest the idea of necessary connection, unquote.

08:26.300 --> 08:31.980
Well, if an idea is a name for a fading experience,

08:31.980 --> 08:36.220
a copy of an experience, and there is no experience of necessary connection,

08:36.220 --> 08:41.860
there is no idea of necessary connection, the phrase must be meaningless.

08:41.860 --> 08:48.140
When, therefore, you take a knife and put it in somebody's heart and twist it.

08:48.140 --> 08:50.940
One event is observing the knife go in, and

08:50.940 --> 08:55.380
the next event is you see the man turn pale and lie down on the ground.

08:55.380 --> 08:59.380
And those are two events that are spatially and temporally contiguous, and

08:59.380 --> 09:00.740
that's it.

09:00.740 --> 09:03.140
You cannot say one made the other happen.

09:04.460 --> 09:07.220
All you have a right to assert, in fact,

09:07.220 --> 09:11.260
the only thing that is meaningful to us is that the two events go together in

09:11.260 --> 09:12.220
space and time.

09:13.940 --> 09:19.300
You observe that one is right next to the other, that one is right after the other,

09:19.300 --> 09:22.540
but you can't observe that one is because of the other.

09:23.660 --> 09:26.860
And of course, that's right, you can't observe the causality.

09:28.700 --> 09:33.100
Well, why do you think that there is a necessary relationship?

09:34.420 --> 09:39.700
If, in fact, this is a myth, again, because you have an overactive imagination.

09:40.700 --> 09:44.740
In this case, you have a hyperactive associative mechanism.

09:46.020 --> 09:49.980
Two events, which in fact have no necessary connection, or

09:49.980 --> 09:52.020
if it would be meaningless to say so.

09:52.020 --> 09:57.100
Two events happen by chance to go together so

09:57.100 --> 10:02.020
many times in your experience, that after a while you form the habit,

10:02.020 --> 10:07.980
simply by custom, by conditioning, to expect the second when you encounter the first.

10:07.980 --> 10:11.980
That is the source of the irrational idea of necessary connection.

10:12.940 --> 10:18.700
You observe, says Hume, repeated conjunctions, repeated conjunctions.

10:18.700 --> 10:22.020
Two events, which happen to go together repeatedly.

10:22.020 --> 10:25.660
And you begin to associate the two and expect the second after the first.

10:25.660 --> 10:29.780
For instance, suppose you were brought up by an irrational mother.

10:30.820 --> 10:35.420
And for no reason at all, every morning when you sat down

10:35.420 --> 10:40.220
by breakfast, at breakfast to drink a glass of orange juice.

10:40.220 --> 10:43.940
Just as you picked the glass of orange juice up, she had a huge strap and

10:43.940 --> 10:46.260
she smashed the kitchen table with it.

10:47.260 --> 10:48.980
Now, on this happened day after day.

10:48.980 --> 10:51.580
There's no causal connection, but that's just the kind of mother you have.

10:53.420 --> 10:58.620
After a while, as you pick up the oranges, you flinch in the expectation of the strap.

10:58.620 --> 11:04.020
And you come to associate the two, you see, simply by quantity of repetition.

11:04.020 --> 11:08.940
Well, Hume says this is exactly the relationship in every case where we

11:08.940 --> 11:09.980
assert causal effect.

11:09.980 --> 11:10.860
That's not his example.

11:12.620 --> 11:17.180
Causality is simply a subjective expectation on our part.

11:17.180 --> 11:20.380
Completely irrational without any justification.

11:22.260 --> 11:27.500
You can use the word cause if you want, but then all it means is

11:27.500 --> 11:32.700
two events are repeatedly conjoined up to now in our experience.

11:32.700 --> 11:38.180
Then we, therefore, have the accompanying irrational, baseless expectation

11:38.180 --> 11:41.420
that there's some connection between them.

11:41.420 --> 11:44.260
But in fact, there is no connection.

11:44.260 --> 11:47.660
I think I have one more quote from Hume on this.

11:52.060 --> 11:53.780
Quote, famous conclusion.

11:54.780 --> 11:59.900
All events seem entirely loose and separate.

11:59.900 --> 12:00.980
Loose and separate.

12:01.940 --> 12:07.460
One event follows another, but we never can observe any tie between them.

12:07.460 --> 12:11.580
They seem conjoined, but never connected.

12:11.580 --> 12:16.860
And as we have no idea of anything which never appeared to our senses,

12:16.860 --> 12:22.660
the conclusion seems to be that we have no idea of connection at all.

12:22.660 --> 12:27.260
And that this word is absolutely without any meaning when employed either in

12:27.260 --> 12:30.460
philosophical reasoning or common life.

12:30.460 --> 12:31.820
Unquote.

12:31.820 --> 12:34.220
That's uncompromising Humean statement.

12:36.060 --> 12:38.700
Now, suppose you can test this and say, oh, that's ridiculous.

12:38.700 --> 12:41.620
Causality is not simply a matter of habit.

12:41.620 --> 12:44.260
Causal sequences are necessary.

12:44.260 --> 12:46.900
Their opposites are literally inconceivable.

12:46.900 --> 12:50.260
We couldn't even imagine their opposites happening.

12:50.260 --> 12:52.940
Hume comes back with a famous example.

12:52.940 --> 12:57.460
He says, you can't perfectly well imagine the opposite happening.

12:58.980 --> 13:03.100
He gives the example of Adam, of course, he doesn't believe in Adam.

13:03.100 --> 13:06.340
Doesn't believe in anything, but it's just as an example of the first man.

13:07.340 --> 13:09.980
Now, Adam across the garden sees a flame.

13:11.980 --> 13:18.140
Is Adam able to know before he experiences the behavior of the flame?

13:18.140 --> 13:22.420
That the flame is going to consume him if he puts his hand into it.

13:23.300 --> 13:27.780
No, he says, Adam hasn't the faintest idea how this orange

13:27.780 --> 13:33.580
tongue that's flickering is going to behave when he puts his hand into it.

13:33.580 --> 13:39.300
Prior to experience, if we asked Adam, is it gonna make you six feet taller,

13:39.300 --> 13:43.020
burn your hand off, or turn you into a pumpkin, Adam would say, I haven't a clue.

13:44.780 --> 13:48.300
Well, it says, Hume, what has he got after experience?

13:48.300 --> 13:50.300
After experience, he's got a burned hand.

13:51.300 --> 13:55.620
But he doesn't have any more understanding of why this took place.

13:55.620 --> 14:00.260
As far as you can see, the fire could just as well have turned him into ice or

14:00.260 --> 14:01.060
into a pumpkin.

14:02.620 --> 14:08.980
In other words, it simply is a matter of brute fact that it happens to be the case

14:08.980 --> 14:13.980
that fire up to now burns or warms.

14:13.980 --> 14:16.940
But it's unintelligible why this is so, and

14:16.940 --> 14:19.700
we can easily conceive the opposite.

14:21.180 --> 14:26.420
Now, if someone were to say that we can explain by reference to scientific law,

14:26.420 --> 14:31.620
why fire does what it does, Hume would say scientific law.

14:31.620 --> 14:34.660
Scientific law is based on cause and effect.

14:34.660 --> 14:37.300
Cause and effect depends on necessary connection, and

14:37.300 --> 14:40.060
that's meaningless, so much for scientific laws.

14:41.620 --> 14:46.340
All we do is we let our familiarity with certain arbitrary

14:46.340 --> 14:51.700
sequences delude us into thinking that the connection is intelligible,

14:51.700 --> 14:53.660
when actually it's completely unintelligible.

14:54.860 --> 14:59.980
Well, suppose you try to give Hume a proof in logic,

14:59.980 --> 15:03.420
that every event must have a cause that necessitates it.

15:05.220 --> 15:08.460
Well, Hume says, go ahead and try, and

15:08.460 --> 15:11.140
I'll show you that you can't give me any such proof.

15:11.140 --> 15:17.100
Is your proof going to rely on reason, he says?

15:17.100 --> 15:20.060
You answer, well, certainly I'm going to give a rational proof.

15:21.340 --> 15:26.220
Well, says Hume, by reason we can only prove truths whose opposites

15:26.220 --> 15:30.900
would be contradictory, logical contradictions.

15:30.900 --> 15:33.660
Reason teaches us that we have to believe something because

15:33.660 --> 15:35.940
the opposite would be a contradiction.

15:35.940 --> 15:39.420
So we can prove that two and two is four because if somebody denied it,

15:39.420 --> 15:41.460
we could show him he was contradicting himself.

15:43.020 --> 15:47.860
Now, anything which is a contradiction is inconceivable.

15:47.860 --> 15:50.340
You can't conceive around square, for instance,

15:50.340 --> 15:52.900
because it's the two sides annihilate each other.

15:54.940 --> 15:59.540
Now, is there any difficulty in conceiving that the law of cause and

15:59.540 --> 16:01.860
effect is false?

16:01.860 --> 16:06.380
Would any contradiction be involved, he asks, in conceiving it?

16:06.380 --> 16:10.500
No, the opposite of the law of cause and effect, he says,

16:10.500 --> 16:12.740
is perfectly conceivable.

16:12.740 --> 16:14.340
It's easy to understand.

16:14.340 --> 16:20.340
It's not like a round square which obliterates it itself.

16:20.340 --> 16:22.500
It's perfectly conceivable.

16:23.700 --> 16:30.140
Take that idea, there are events which don't have any causes.

16:30.140 --> 16:34.900
Now, if this was a contradiction, we shouldn't even be able to grasp it.

16:34.900 --> 16:36.540
It should be like married bachelor.

16:37.540 --> 16:40.820
But says, Hume, there's no difficulty in grasping this.

16:40.820 --> 16:43.780
Just imagine, I'm making up the example, but this is his idea.

16:43.780 --> 16:46.700
Imagine you're walking down the street and

16:46.700 --> 16:51.860
suddenly an apple pops into existence out of thin air.

16:51.860 --> 16:54.980
Nothing preceded it, it's not a hallucination.

16:54.980 --> 16:58.060
It just is there without any cause.

16:58.060 --> 16:59.260
Walt Disney could drop.

17:00.980 --> 17:04.140
Now says, Hume, this is perfectly conceivable.

17:04.140 --> 17:05.660
There's no contradiction in it.

17:05.660 --> 17:07.780
If there were a contradiction, you couldn't conceive it.

17:07.780 --> 17:11.300
But you understood my story, so you must be able to conceive it.

17:11.300 --> 17:14.140
Whereas if I said a round square popped out,

17:14.140 --> 17:15.500
you'd say, I don't know what that is.

17:16.820 --> 17:19.380
If it's conceivable, there's no contradiction.

17:19.380 --> 17:22.380
If there's no contradiction, reason can't prove it.

17:22.380 --> 17:25.580
Reason only proves something whose opposite is a contradiction.

17:25.580 --> 17:29.700
Therefore, the law of cause and effect cannot be proved.

17:29.700 --> 17:32.100
Since it can't be proved in reason, and

17:32.100 --> 17:36.140
we know there's no basis for it in reference to experience,

17:37.180 --> 17:42.060
we conclude the law of cause and effect is bereft of any foundation of any kind.

17:42.060 --> 17:47.380
In reason or in experience, it is therefore simply a myth.

17:49.900 --> 17:56.420
Now, of course, the objections to this Humean viewpoint are legion.

17:56.420 --> 17:59.380
Since this is the last time I'll get my licks in it,

17:59.380 --> 18:03.300
you might keep interrupting each point because I can't put it off anymore

18:03.300 --> 18:05.340
that, of course, having running out.

18:05.340 --> 18:06.860
But let me just indicate briefly.

18:08.300 --> 18:13.660
Notice that Hume assumes that if he can visualize an event that takes place

18:13.660 --> 18:18.580
allegedly without a cause, that that's the same as saying he conceives it

18:18.580 --> 18:19.700
without contradiction.

18:20.660 --> 18:24.620
Now, of course, if Aristotle heard this argument, he would say,

18:25.620 --> 18:29.900
you are visualizing an event which implies a contradiction.

18:30.900 --> 18:34.980
And therefore, you are actually conceiving nothing but an irrational

18:34.980 --> 18:37.460
figment of your own imagination.

18:37.460 --> 18:40.860
You have an image, but not a logical concept.

18:41.860 --> 18:43.900
What would Hume's answer be if he heard that?

18:45.260 --> 18:46.380
What's the difference?

18:47.620 --> 18:49.460
An image is a concept.

18:49.460 --> 18:53.060
If I can form an image of something, I've formed a concept of it.

18:53.260 --> 18:56.100
That, of course, is his nominalism.

18:56.100 --> 18:57.500
Concept is an image.

18:58.420 --> 19:01.060
So if you can form an image, you can form a concept.

19:01.060 --> 19:05.100
And if you can form a concept, then it's obviously logically possible.

19:05.100 --> 19:10.260
Therefore, if you can form an image, any arbitrary fantastic image,

19:10.260 --> 19:13.220
the thing it stands for is logically possible.

19:13.220 --> 19:18.300
That is the end result of reducing concepts to images the way the nominalists do.

19:18.300 --> 19:24.940
Now, you might think you would satisfy Hume if you gave him the proof of cause and

19:24.940 --> 19:27.340
effect that we developed from Aristotle's philosophy.

19:28.380 --> 19:31.620
You remember the argument which had essentially two premises.

19:31.620 --> 19:36.300
Actions are actions of entities, and entities have identity.

19:36.300 --> 19:39.820
They are what they are, the law of identity, and therefore,

19:39.820 --> 19:43.980
to make a long story short, they can only act in accordance with their nature.

19:43.980 --> 19:49.900
Now, if you were to reincarnate David Hume and give him this argument,

19:49.900 --> 19:52.220
he wouldn't bat an eye or turn a hair.

19:53.820 --> 20:01.020
Because observe each premise, entities, he would say, what is that?

20:01.020 --> 20:04.700
All we have are loose, floating bundles of qualities.

20:04.700 --> 20:08.660
And that's all that he as a nominalist sensualist can encounter.

20:08.660 --> 20:13.500
And therefore, the premise about entities existing is already out.

20:13.500 --> 20:17.580
And so is therefore the base of any proof of cause and effect given his nominalist.

20:17.580 --> 20:23.340
And as for the law of identity, is that supposed to be a necessary general truth?

20:23.340 --> 20:27.820
Well, then, as a nominalist, that, of course, must be linguistic,

20:27.820 --> 20:29.980
semantic, just the way you use words.

20:29.980 --> 20:31.100
It doesn't say anything.

20:32.060 --> 20:38.620
Now, you see, in other words, causality has already comes fairly far down a philosophy.

20:38.620 --> 20:44.540
You first of all have to have the conceptual level to validate your knowledge of anything,

20:44.540 --> 20:45.980
including of causality.

20:47.180 --> 20:52.700
So there's actually nothing new to answer in Hume's attack on cause and effect.

20:52.700 --> 20:58.220
If you can answer his nominalism and sensualism, if you can defend a valid theory of concepts,

20:58.860 --> 21:02.380
then his whole attack on cause and effect crashes to the ground,

21:02.380 --> 21:04.300
along with the whole rest of his philosophy.

21:04.940 --> 21:08.620
And of course, if you cannot answer his nominalism and sensualism,

21:09.180 --> 21:12.460
then you are lost and everything is lost.

21:13.180 --> 21:19.020
